In England, in the seven days to 15 February, there were 269,660 new confirmed cases (476.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 February, there were 400,154 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (130,494 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 February is 15,859,074 (28,044.3 cases per 100,000 population).
